text:
Can anyone give me some advice or hints for optimising loading scripts in my modules? I have several modules that share resources - for example I am pulling in a swiper CSS and JS in to my meta.json file, and I have a few different modules that use those same files. I have applied `render_options` to the CSS and JS but this does not seem to affect `assets` only the module JS CSS file. How do I add loading options to files in `css_assets` and `js_assets`? The autoload option seems undocumented, and doesn't seem to make any difference if its true or false. Any tips?

```{
    "css_assets": [
        {
            "autoload": false,
            "path": "../css/ondemand/swiper-bundle.min.css",
            "name": "swiper-bundle.min.css"
        }
    ],
    "js_assets": [
        {
            "autoload": false,
            "path": "../js/ondemand/swiper-bundle.min.js",
            "name": "swiper-bundle.min.js"
        }
    ],
    "js_render_options": {
        "position": "header",
        "async": false,
        "defer": true
    },
    "css_render_options": {
        "async": true
    }
}```
